      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory-core): reset lastMetaSerialized in runSafeReindex so a byte-identical reindex still writes __meta",
        "body": "## Problem\nOn agents with high reindex traffic, `memory_search` reports `Index identity: missing -> Vector search: paused -> falls back to FTS` immediately after a *successful* `--index`.\n\nRoot cause: `runSafeReindex` swaps `this.db = tempDb`, but the `this.lastMetaSerialized` guard is reset inside `resetVectorState()` — and `resetVectorState()` did not clear it. So when a reindex recomputes byte-identical metadata, the `writeMeta` INSERT is skipped (the guard thinks nothing changed) and the atomic swap installs a fresh temp DB with **no `__meta` row**. The manager then reads \"identity missing\" and pauses vector search (the paused recall path early-returns and never re-evaluates), silently degrading to FTS until a hard process restart.\n\n## Fix\nReset `this.lastMetaSerialized = null` in `resetVectorState()` (called right after `this.db = tempDb` in `runSafeReindex`), so `writeMeta` always stamps `__meta` into the fresh temp DB. One line.\n\n## Test\nAdds a regression test: prime `lastMetaSerialized`, run a byte-identical `runSafeReindex`, assert the post-swap DB has a `__meta` row. Red before the fix, green after; targeted memory-core suite stays green.\n\n## Note\nA separate, deferred follow-up (not in this PR): make the paused recall path self-heal / re-evaluate identity in-process so a stuck manager recovers without a hard restart.\n",
        "branch": "fix/memory-index-identity-meta-stamp",
        "head_sha": "81860f7c59ea3771e5b275b8d956331af02998f8",
        "author": "yarikv8",
